This paper deals with natural language parsing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of counts and dependencies, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing data and making predictions, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS).
